featured_reviews.review_id:
The mosque belong to a sect in Islam called Tableegi jamaat. There were more than 2 muezzin for the mosque maintenance and delivering azaan ( a call for prayer). Also found few staff as well for maintenance of cleanliness. The washrooms are very clean and are washed at regular intervals in a day.
CCTVs are also installed wherever necessary. There are separate stands built for footwear as well.
The mosque is beautifully decorated with many Islamic quotations and Quranic verses on the walls. Mosque is Air conditioned.

Irritating thing is that, a guy in charge of the water and cleanliness section comes and keeps telling not to waste the water.
The visitors  are fed up about the authourity about this.

Literally speaking, why would one,  waste water?

Isn't it insane?

Apparently no one wastes water , but you would still find this guy irritating the visitors creating annoyance.

Other than this, " All is well ".
